Actress Mo Bimpe surprised her hubby of two- months Abdulateef Adedimeji with a close-knit birthday party on Tuesday Abdullateef turned 36 on Tuesday and the party was held in the comfort of their Lagos home. Some of the celebrities that attended the close-knit birthday surprise include Woli Arole, Jide Awobona, Okiki Afolayan, Aisha Lawal, Eniola Ajao and Adebowale Seilat amongst others. Abdulateef was all smiles as he shook hands and hugged many he didn’t expect in his house for the surprise party.   I am frantically praying for a daughter-in-law, says…     Top ranking African countries in the music industries     I can’t wait to experience pregnancy – Ex-BBN’s Mercy Eke   In his gratitude speech, the movie star said: “It feels good to have people around, those that genuinely care, those that go out of their way to show love and care, I feel honored and till this minute I still feel goosebumps all over me, how do I say thank you? - Advertisement - “Yesterday opened my eyes to a lot of things, many of you left your personal routines to make my day even at very short notice, the surprise birthday party was lit and everyone present made me feel special beyond words.” He said: “The kind words every one of you said will continue to ring in my head, the gifts remain special just as the pure intentions behind them, I could go on and on and words will only fail me, in every language I understand I’m saying a heartfelt thank you.” Taking out time to shower encomiums on his wife, he said: “And to you, Bimpe, my very own Rahmah, thank you, my woman, you keep outdoing yourself, you keep pulling your stunts in majestic ways, you’re the true definition of the Comforter God promised me, thank you and… I won’t say it, wait for it.”